 Islam than the reductivist narrative of the religion that became commonplace in the mainstream Western media after the events of September 11th.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aIslam -- Doctrines -- Southeast Asia. 0aTablighi Jamaʿat. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978908964439840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048516827?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048516827zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048516827/original  a978-3-11-060651-5 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8 Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1 AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA